Architecture Overview
Flow Stages:
Stage 1: Raw Data Ingestion
S3 Bucket: dz-demo-mt
Paths:
raw/sales/ - Sales transaction data
raw/region/ - Regional reference data
Stage 2: Metadata Discovery
Crawler: sales-mt-tst → Scans raw/sales/
Crawler: region-mt-tst → Scans raw/region/
Catalog Tables:
sal_sales - Sales table schema
reg_region - Region table schema
Stage 3: ETL Processing
Glue Job: dz-mt-tst
Reads from both catalog tables
Performs join operation
Applies transformations and aggregations
Writes results to processed layer
Stage 4: Catalog Update
Output Path: processed/sales_joined/
Catalog Table: sal_join_stg
Partitioning: year/month/day for efficient querying
Stage 5: Cross-Region Replication
Source Region: us-east-1
Target Region: us-east-2
Replication Scope: processed/sales_joined/ directory
Purpose: Disaster recovery and multi-region access
